 057:     # Don't derive from str
 058:     # follow pathlib.Path design
 059:     # probably URL will not suffer from pathlib problems:
 060:     # it's intended for libraries like aiohttp,
 061:     # not to be passed into standard library functions like os.open etc.
 062: 
 063:     # URL grammar (RFC 3986)
 064:     # pct-encoded = "%" HEXDIG HEXDIG
 065:     # reserved    = gen-delims / sub-delims
 066:     # gen-delims  = ":" / "/" / "?" / "#" / "[" / "]" / "@"
 067:     # sub-delims  = "!" / "$" / "&" / "'" / "(" / ")"
 068:     #             / "*" / "+" / "," / ";" / "="
 069:     # unreserved  = ALPHA / DIGIT / "-" / "." / "_" / "~"
 070:     # URI         = scheme ":" hier-part [ "?" query ] [ "#" fragment ]
 071:     # hier-part   = "//" authority path-abempty
 072:     #             / path-absolute
 073:     #             / path-rootless
 074:     #             / path-empty
 075:     # scheme      = ALPHA *( ALPHA / DIGIT / "+" / "-" / "." )
 076:     # authority   = [ userinfo "@" ] host [ ":" port ]
 077:     # userinfo    = *( unreserved / pct-encoded / sub-delims / ":" )
 078:     # host        = IP-literal / IPv4address / reg-name
 079:     # IP-literal = "[" ( IPv6address / IPvFuture  ) "]"
 080:     # IPvFuture  = "v" 1*HEXDIG "." 1*( unreserved / sub-delims / ":" )
 081:     # IPv6address =                            6( h16 ":" ) ls32
 082:     #             /                       "::" 5( h16 ":" ) ls32
 083:     #             / [               h16 ] "::" 4( h16 ":" ) ls32
 084:     #             / [ *1( h16 ":" ) h16 ] "::" 3( h16 ":" ) ls32
 085:     #             / [ *2( h16 ":" ) h16 ] "::" 2( h16 ":" ) ls32
 086:     #             / [ *3( h16 ":" ) h16 ] "::"    h16 ":"   ls32
 087:     #             / [ *4( h16 ":" ) h16 ] "::"              ls32
 088:     #             / [ *5( h16 ":" ) h16 ] "::"              h16
 089:     #             / [ *6( h16 ":" ) h16 ] "::"
 090:     # ls32        = ( h16 ":" h16 ) / IPv4address
 091:     #             ; least-significant 32 bits of address
 092:     # h16         = 1*4HEXDIG
 093:     #             ; 16 bits of address represented in hexadecimal
 094:     # IPv4address = dec-octet "." dec-octet "." dec-octet "." dec-octet
 095:     # dec-octet   = DIGIT                 ; 0-9
 096:     #             / %x31-39 DIGIT         ; 10-99
 097:     #             / "1" 2DIGIT            ; 100-199
 098:     #             / "2" %x30-34 DIGIT     ; 200-249
 099:     #             / "25" %x30-35          ; 250-255
 100:     # reg-name    = *( unreserved / pct-encoded / sub-delims )
 101:     # port        = *DIGIT
 102:     # path          = path-abempty    ; begins with "/" or is empty
 103:     #               / path-absolute   ; begins with "/" but not "//"
 104:     #               / path-noscheme   ; begins with a non-colon segment
 105:     #               / path-rootless   ; begins with a segment
 106:     #               / path-empty      ; zero characters
 107:     # path-abempty  = *( "/" segment )
 108:     # path-absolute = "/" [ segment-nz *( "/" segment ) ]
 109:     # path-noscheme = segment-nz-nc *( "/" segment )
 110:     # path-rootless = segment-nz *( "/" segment )
 111:     # path-empty    = 0<pchar>
 112:     # segment       = *pchar
 113:     # segment-nz    = 1*pchar
 114:     # segment-nz-nc = 1*( unreserved / pct-encoded / sub-delims / "@" )
 115:     #               ; non-zero-length segment without any colon ":"
 116:     # pchar         = unreserved / pct-encoded / sub-delims / ":" / "@"
 117:     # query       = *( pchar / "/" / "?" )
 118:     # fragment    = *( pchar / "/" / "?" )
 119:     # URI-reference = URI / relative-ref
 120:     # relative-ref  = relative-part [ "?" query ] [ "#" fragment ]
 121:     # relative-part = "//" authority path-abempty
 122:     #               / path-absolute
 123:     #               / path-noscheme
 124:     #               / path-empty
 125:     # absolute-URI  = scheme ":" hier-part [ "?" query ]
+126:     __slots__ = ("_cache", "_val")
